This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with Internet traffic analysis and network management. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the study of traffic matrix decomposition models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with network traffic patterns. The paper also involves numerical algorithms and simulations, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
